marklogic.body:
My scores were not much better. I tried doing it yesterday, and got 32 squat jumps, 14 pushups and 6 burpees in before I had to stop. I had gotten maybe 3 hours of sleep in the past two days and had ran a mile that morning, and my body was just...done in. Here are my scores for my second attempt compared to the most recent of my older scores:Â
(Old/New) (1) 32 vs 32/27 (2) 20 vs 14/10 (3) 10 vs 6/11 (4) 160 vs 132 (5) 12 vs 12 (6) 9 vs 12 (7) n/a vs 12 (8) 16 vs 18Â
I would have thought that my scores would be much better than this - but I do have a lot of stress in my life right now, so that may be playing a role. Also, my diet has not been clean. Any time I hang out with friends, my diet ends up going to shit. So, I am starting a food diary today, and I have to have a clean diet because I am working my ass and not losing weight, and it's really starting to piss me Off - and 70% of Weight loss is diet, and I am failing on that front. So, hopefully I can keep my diet super clean for at least a few weeks. I want to see my muscles!!! Oh, but I did find this thing on Pinterest that said, "Don't treat yourself with food, you're not a dog!" I love that, so I figured I'd share. :D
Thanks guys!Â
